    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-02-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-02-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="398"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                <head>398. Memorandum For the Record by the Deputy Executive Secretary of the
                    Department of State (Miller)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d398fn1">Source:
                        National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files
                        1970–73, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 16 BANGLADESH. Top Secret;
                        Nodis.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d398fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HBMJ1">General Haig</persName> called the Department
                        with the instruction that nothing be done concerning recognition of
                        Bangladesh until President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>
                        returned from China. Contacts with Bangladesh officials were to be kept to a
                        minimum.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1972-02-22"
                        >February 22, 1972</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>General <persName corresp="#p_HBMJ1">Haig</persName> called this morning to relay
                    the following message from the Presidential party with regard to the issue of
                    Bangladesh recognition: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Nothing should be done regarding the recognition issue before the
                            return of the Presidential party.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Contacts with Bangladesh officials should be held to a minimum.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Any such contacts should be only related to relief questions.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Robert H. Miller</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
